casebody.data:
Benjamin WEATHINGTON, Petitioner-Appellant, v. Louie L. WAINWRIGHT, Secretary, Department of Offender Rehabilitation, Respondent-Appellee. No. 79-2501

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 31, 1980. Thomas G. Murray, Asst. Public Defender, 11th Judicial Circuit of Fla., Miami, Fla., for petitioner-appellant. Joel D. Rosenblatt, Florida Regional Service Center, Miami, Fla., for respondent-appellee.

Before AINSWORTH, FAY and RANDALL, Circuit Judges.

Fed.R.App.P. 34(a); 5th Cir. R. 18.

 PER CURIAM:

The denial of relief is affirmed for those reasons set forth in Judge Eaton’s Order of Dismissal dated May 21, 1979 and reported at 486 F.Supp. 934.
